addOverlay

public static org.eclipse.swt.graphics.Image addOverlay(org.eclipse.swt.graphics.Image image,
                                                        org.eclipse.swt.graphics.RGB color)
Creates an overlay dot at the bottom right of the given image. The dot is offset at 1px from the right-most and bottom-most non-transparent pixel of the image. Evaluation of the right-most and bottom-most non-transparent pixel is performed by reading left from the center of the image y axis and up from the center of the image x axis respectively.

Parameters:
image - The image that the overlay will be added to
color - The color that the overlay should be.
Returns:
